F/WyKoFoE7adUeuAdAY7hI69yJ4Iork87ZJANACr17Lk
  "],
 CellID->1305404242],

Cell[TextData[{
 "where ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["m", TraditionalForm]], "InlineMath"],
 " equals the number of lunar cycles per revolution about the Sun. (For the \
Sun-Earth-Moon system, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"m", "\[TildeTilde]", "13"}], TraditionalForm]], "InlineMath"],
 ".) These represent parametric equations for epitroichoids, which reduce to \
the more familiar epicycloids when ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"m", "=", 
    RowBox[{"R", "/", "a", " "}]}], TraditionalForm]], "InlineMath"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"m", "=", 
    RowBox[{"R", "/", "b", " "}]}], TraditionalForm]], "InlineMath"],
 " in the first and second set of equations, respectively. In most cases \
these curves exhibit a looped or cuspoid structure as they traverse the \
larger circle. All rotations and revolutions shown are counterclockwise."
}], "ManipulateCaption",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.5441374760524282`*^9, 3.544137593569433*^9}, {
   3.544137628781681*^9, 3.5441378537220507`*^9}, {3.5441378853012257`*^9, 
   3.5441379724733963`*^9}, {3.5441381323965673`*^9, 3.54413818119878*^9}, {
   3.544138214330649*^9, 3.544138248394665*^9}, {3.544138666424518*^9, 
   3.5441389301305857`*^9}, {3.544138986888008*^9, 3.544139002557199*^9}, {
   3.544139044813114*^9, 3.544139129305778*^9}, {3.544139178800358*^9, 
   3.544139197588026*^9}, {3.544139229980057*^9, 3.5441393111478167`*^9}, {
   3.544139353848302*^9, 3.5441393835182*^9}, {3.544139413871212*^9, 
   3.544139419779499*^9}, {3.5441394731764183`*^9, 3.544139473184369*^9}, {
   3.544139661577588*^9, 3.5441396705741253`*^9}, 3.544140356467063*^9, 
   3.544187475190153*^9, {3.544311123214304*^9, 3.544311197306535*^9}, {
   3.544311332424597*^9, 3.544311332434905*^9}, {3.54431138989717*^9, 
   3.54431142102205*^9}, {3.544464352939966*^9, 3.544464352939966*^9}, 
   3.544541469092579*^9, {3.545483923177352*^9, 3.545483923653322*^9}},
 CellID->2122482405],

Cell[TextData[{
 "This brings us to the remarkable fact that the Moon's orbit around the Sun \
is a convex curve. This can be explained by the following physical argument. \
The gravitational force of the Sun on the Moon is always more than twice the \
gravitational force of the Earth on the Moon: ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"|", 
    FractionBox[
     RowBox[{"G", " ", "M", " ", 
      RowBox[{
       SubscriptBox["m", 
        RowBox[{"a", " "}]], "/", 
       SuperscriptBox["R", "2"]}]}], 
     RowBox[{"G", " ", 
      SubscriptBox["m", "a"], 
      RowBox[{
       SubscriptBox["m", "b"], "/", 
       SuperscriptBox["r", "2"], " "}]}]], "|", 
    RowBox[{"\[TildeTilde]", "2.21"}]}], TraditionalForm]], "InlineMath"],
 ". Thus the net force on the Moon is always directed toward the Sun. But, by \
Newton's second law, this force is proportional to the second derivative of \
",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["r", TraditionalForm]], "InlineMath"],
 " with respect to time, hence the radial curvature of the orbit is always \
positive. This implies that the Moon\[CloseCurlyQuote]s orbit is always \
convex with respect to the Sun. In terms of the epitrochoid parameters, the \
condition for convexity can be expressed as ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"R", "/", "a"}], " ", "\[GreaterEqual]", " ", 
    SuperscriptBox["m", "2"]}], TraditionalForm]], "InlineMath"],
 ", which is easily fulfilled for the Sun and Moon. Remarkably, no other \
known planet-moon couple in the Solar System obeys the convexity condition."
}], "ManipulateCaption",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.544121670183551*^9, 3.544122003943324*^9}, {
   3.544122062966428*^9, 3.544122088369425*^9}, {3.544122130645185*^9, 
   3.544122211129424*^9}, {3.544122272741274*^9, 3.54412242052143*^9}, {
   3.544122460927*^9, 3.544122463961659*^9}, {3.544123519526031*^9, 
   3.544123528600963*^9}, {3.5441397006257963`*^9, 3.544139784394923*^9}, {
   3.544140164353137*^9, 3.5441401867888517`*^9}, {3.5441402223296967`*^9, 
   3.544140224197147*^9}, {3.544140266148797*^9, 3.5441402936147013`*^9}, {
   3.544141584877289*^9, 3.5441417719392433`*^9}, {3.544141802505686*^9, 
   3.544141888100189*^9}, {3.544141953832283*^9, 3.54414202975811*^9}, {
   3.544187527831769*^9, 3.544187531363111*^9}, 3.544311449125689*^9, {
   3.544363303459394*^9, 3.544363307894496*^9}, {3.544363372502658*^9, 
